article.headline: N. Iowa 61, Iowa St. 48
article.story: AMES, Iowa (AP) -- Jared Josten scored 20 points and Northern Iowa beat Iowa State 61-48 Tuesday, snapping a four-game road losing streak against the Cyclones. Eric Coleman added 10 points and 14 rebounds for the Panthers (5-1), who outscored Iowa State 30-10 down the stretch and picked up their first win at Hilton Coliseum since 1997. Josten helped Northern Iowa pull away with two key baskets late in the game. He followed a jumper with a 3 off the backboard with 3:34 left, giving the Panthers a 51-45 lead. Northern Iowa's defense did the rest, holding Iowa State (2-3) scoreless until the game was well in hand. Wesley Johnson -- in his first game back after suffering a bone bruise in his foot -- scored 18 points to lead Iowa State, which has lost three straight. Northern Iowa held freshman forward Craig Brackins, Iowa State's leading scorer, to two points. Down five after a lackluster first half, Iowa State went on a 12-0 run to take a 38-31 lead. The Cyclones held Northern Iowa scoreless for the opening 7:12 of the second half and pounded the glass offensively, as inside baskets from Rahshon Clark and Jiri Hubalek highlighted the spurt. Northern Iowa, helped by its first two 3s of the game, regained the lead with 5:15 left. Kerwin Dunham banked one in to tie the game at 41, and Travis Brown's 3 put Northern Iowa back ahead for good 46-43. Johnson got the Cyclones on the right track, scoring six quick points to give Iowa State an early lead, but Brackins picked up his second foul five minutes in and sat for the rest of the half. The Panthers took advantage with a 14-0 run, capped by a Lucas O'Rear drive that made it 18-10 midway through the first half. Panthers coach Ben Jacobson, who was the top assistant under Iowa State coach Greg McDermott at Northern Iowa, is now 2-0 against the Cyclones. Clark and Hubalek each had 10 points for Iowa State.
